{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3ddb2ed8-673f-432e-93bb-f257520da462","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but I can tell you exactly what's needed to publish a C# MCP server as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\nAdd these to your `MyMcpServer.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — marks it as a dotnet tool (this is the key property).\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users will run.\n- **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — tools must be console apps.\n\n### Pack & Publish\n\n```bash\ndotnet pack -c Release\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\n### MCP client config (e.g. VS Code)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"command\": \"my-mcp-server\",\n      \"transport\": \"stdio\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThat's the minimum. Want me to create or update your actual `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c576c529-7320-47a6-9627-383aec4efcf1","outputTokens":494,"requestId":"3C01:20AC41:1F6BA0F:2356654:69E81D56"},"id":"96c3a3f6-c6d6-4092-be78-72885f415880","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:59:11.534Z","parentId":"6d955939-cc80-436b-86ee-ee1db00ebc80"}
